statements.sql: select column_name as `column_name` from information_schema.columns where table_schema = 'laravel' and table_name = 'roles'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` = 2 and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\User'
select * from `restorants` where `restorants`.`user_id` = 2 and `restorants`.`user_id` is not null limit 1
select count(*) as aggregate from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2021-03-23 12:32:04' and `restorant_id` = 1)
select sum(`order_price`) as aggregate from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2021-03-23 12:32:04' and `restorant_id` = 1 and `payment_status` = 'paid')

select SUM(order_price + delivery_price) AS sumValue from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2020-10-01 00:00:00' and `restorant_id` = 1 and `payment_status` = 'paid') group by YEAR(created_at), MONTH(created_at) order by YEAR(created_at), MONTH(created_at) asc

select MONTH(created_at) as month from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2020-10-01 00:00:00' and `restorant_id` = 1) group by YEAR(created_at), MONTH(created_at) order by YEAR(created_at), MONTH(created_at) asc

select count(id) as totalPerMonth from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2020-10-01 00:00:00' and `restorant_id` = 1) group by YEAR(created_at), MONTH(created_at) order by YEAR(created_at), MONTH(created_at) asc
select sum(`delivery_price`) as aggregate from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2021-03-23 12:32:04' and `restorant_id` = 1)
select sum(`static_fee`) as aggregate from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2021-03-23 12:32:04' and `restorant_id` = 1)
select sum(`fee_value`) as aggregate from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2021-03-23 12:32:04' and `restorant_id` = 1)
select SUM(delivery_price + static_fee + fee_value) AS sumValue from `orders` where (`created_at` > '2021-03-23 12:32:04' and `restorant_id` = 1) limit 1
select * from `categories` where `categories`.`restorant_id` = 1 and `categories`.`restorant_id` is not null and (`categories`.`active` = 1) order by `order_index` asc
select count(*) as aggregate from `items` where `category_id` in (1, 2, 3, 4) and `items`.`deleted_at` is null
